  "metadata": {
    "modules": [
      {
        "name": "QuickTime File Format"
      }
    ],
    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Graphics modes"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Graphics modes are also known as transfer modes. Some graphics modes require a color to be specified for certain operations, such as blending to determine the blend level. QuickTime uses the graphics modes defined by Apple’s QuickDraw.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The most common graphics modes are and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "ditherCopy",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", which simply indicate that the image should not blend with the image behind it, but overwrite it. QuickTime also defines several additional graphics modes.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The following table lists the additional graphics modes supported by QuickTime.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "header": "row",
          "rows": [
            [
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Mode",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Uses opcolor",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Code",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Description",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Copy",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "code": "0x0",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Copy the source image over the destination.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Dither copy",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "code": "0x40",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Dither the image (if needed), otherwise do a copy.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Blend",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "yes",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "code": "0x20",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Replaces destination pixel with a blend of the source and destination pixel colors, with the proportion for each channel controlled by that channel in the opcolor.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Transparent",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "yes",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "code": "0x24",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Replaces the destination pixel with the source pixel if the source pixel isn’t equal to the opcolor.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Straight alpha",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "code": "0x100",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Replaces the destination pixel with a blend of the source and destination pixels, with the proportion controlled by the alpha channel.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Premul white alpha",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "code": "0x101",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Premultiplied with white means that the color components of each pixel have already been blended with a white pixel, based on their alpha channel value. Effectively, this means that the image has already been combined with a white background. First, remove the white from each pixel and then blend the image with the actual background pixels.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Premul black alpha",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "code": "0x102",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Premultiplied with black is the same as pre-multiplied with white, except the background color that the image has been blended with is black instead of white.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Straight alpha blend",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "yes",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "code": "0x104",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Similar to straight alpha, but the alpha value used for each channel is the combination of the alpha channel and that channel in the opcolor.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Composition (dither copy)",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "code": "0x103",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "(Tracks only) The track is drawn offscreen, and then composed onto the screen using dither copy.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            ]
          ],
          "type": "table"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
